We just include the jar and use these classes.  No need of source.

I would suggest you hang on the jetty site just to see what it takes 
setting it up ssl.

SimpleHttpServer encapsulates our interaction with Jetty.

Here is set up of an ssl listener from commented out section of default 
jetty.xml:


  &lt;!-- - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - --&gt;
  &lt;!-- Add a HTTPS SSL listener on port 8443                           --&gt;
  &lt;!-- - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - --&gt;
  &lt;!-- UNCOMMENT TO ACTIVATE
  &lt;Call name=&quot;addListener&quot;&gt;
    &lt;Arg&gt;
      &lt;New class=&quot;org.mortbay.http.SunJsseListener&quot;&gt;
        &lt;Set name=&quot;Port&quot;&gt;8443&lt;/Set&gt;
        &lt;Set name=&quot;PoolName&quot;&gt;main&lt;/Set&gt;
        &lt;Set name=&quot;Keystore&quot;&gt;&lt;SystemProperty name=&quot;jetty.home&quot;
            default=&quot;.&quot;/&gt;/etc/demokeystore&lt;/Set&gt;
    &lt;Set name=&quot;Password&quot;&gt;OBF:1vny1zlo1x8e1vnw1vn61x8g1zlu1vn4&lt;/Set&gt;
    &lt;Set name=&quot;KeyPassword&quot;&gt;OBF:1u2u1wml1z7s1z7a1wnl1u2g&lt;/Set&gt;
        &lt;Set name=&quot;NonPersistentUserAgent&quot;&gt;MSIE 5&lt;/Set&gt;
      &lt;/New&gt;
    &lt;/Arg&gt;
  &lt;/Call&gt;
  --&gt;

So, optionally at line 
http://crawler.archive.org/xref/org/archive/crawler/SimpleHttpServer.html#97, 
I&#39;d imagine that optionally, you&#39;d make this listener be a 
SunJsseListener rather than just a SocketListener (Check that this is 
the listener that uses the JVMs ssl -- not a providers -- because jetty 
has support for both.  You can assume at least jvm 1.4 because heritrix 
does).

Regards keystore, see &#39;2.2.3.3. javax.net.ssl.trustStore&#39;, 
http://crawler.archive.org/articles/user_manual.html.  It may be of some 
use.

